source.description: Financial Industry Business Ontology (FIBO) - Complete Production T-Box from EDM Council

entities.name: Account
entities.description: container for records associated with a business arrangement for regular transactions and services

entities.name: AccountHolder
entities.description: party that owns an account

entities.name: AccountingFramework
entities.description: framework, including policies, methods, rules, and processes, used to measure, recognize, present, and disclose the information appearing in an entity's financial statements, and, from a legal ownership perspective, that is applied for accounting consolidation determination

entities.name: AccountingTransaction
entities.description: event recognized by an entry in the records of an account

entities.name: AccountOwnership
entities.description: holding of an account

entities.name: AccountProvider
entities.description: party that provides and services an account

entities.name: AccountSpecificServiceAgreement
entities.description: service-agreement that is account-specific, applicable in cases where a client might hold multiple accounts with differing terms and conditions

entities.name: Accrual
entities.description: the process of accumulating interest or other income that has been earned but not paid

description._: event announced, initiated or carried out by an organization that affects a legal entity or the securities it issues and may have a material impact on that entity's stakeholders, such as shareholders and creditors

entities.name: ActionClassificationScheme
entities.description: scheme for classifying the kinds of actions and events that may be announced, initiated or carried out by an organization that affects a legal entity or the securities it issues

description._: classifier that distinguishes the kinds of actions and events that may be announced, initiated or carried out by an organization that affects a legal entity or the securities it issues, such as income-oriented events

entities.name: Actor
entities.description: primary performer in a relationship between parties, i.e., the party that does something, causes something to happen, or otherwise plays an agentive role in the relationship

description._: amended closing price to reflect a security's value after accounting for any corporate actions, such as stock splits, dividends, and rights offerings

entities.name: Adult
entities.description: person who has attained the age of majority as defined in some jurisdiction

entities.name: Affiliate
entities.description: party that is related to a legal entity, directly, or indirectly through one or more intermediaries, and controls, or is controlled by, or is under common control with that entity, typically determined by the degree of ownership

entities.name: AgencyAgreement
entities.description: agreement that designates a party as a registered agent to represent and act on behalf of another party in some, typically legal, financial, or medical capacity

entities.name: Agent
entities.description: something autonomous that can adapt to and interact with its environment

entities.name: AgentForServiceOfProcess
entities.description: registered agent (person or organization) designated by a business entity, such as a corporation, to receive legal correspondence on behalf of the business entity in the jurisdiction in which the agent's address is located

entities.name: Agreement
entities.description: negotiated understanding between two or more parties, reflecting the offer and acceptance of commitments on the part of either party

description._: negotiable commodity that is obtained via some agricultural process, including forestry, fishing, livestock, grain, dairy, corn, cocoa, soybeans, sugar, coffee
a digraph representing a country or geographic region
a trigraph representing a country or geographic region

entities.name: Amortization
entities.description: the process of reduction of debt or other costs through periodic charges to assets or liabilities, such as through principal payments on mortgages

entities.name: AmortizingBond
entities.description: bond that regularly pays down the principal (face value) on the debt along with its interest expense over the life of the bond

entities.name: Appraiser
entities.description: party that evaluates or estimates the nature, quality, ability, or value of someone or something

entities.name: ApprovedPublicationArrangement
entities.description: data reporting services provider that is authorized to provide the service of publishing certain trade reports on behalf of banks, investment firms, or asset management companies

entities.name: ApprovedReportingMechanism
entities.description: data reporting services provider that is authorized to provide the service of reporting details of transactions to competent authorities or ESMA (the European Securities and Markets Authority) on behalf of investment firms

entities.name: ArbitraryUnit
entities.description: arbitrarily defined unit of measurement, where a relation of the unit to a physical unit of the SI does not exist or is unknown

entities.name: Arrangement
entities.description: systematic plan, manner, or method for making, doing, achieving, or organizing something

entities.name: ArticlesOfIncorporation
entities.description: contract that establishes a new corporation or, when amended, adjusts the legal basis for the corporation, and outlines basic information about the corporation, including the type of business, and a description of the business' operational characteristics

entities.name: Aspect
entities.description: characteristic or feature that can be used to dimensionalize, filter, or subset a class, collection, or set of things

entities.name: AssessmentActivity
entities.description: activity involving the evaluation or estimation of the nature, quality, ability, or value of someone or something

entities.name: AssessmentBoundary
entities.description: defined scope, limits, and criteria used to determine what is included or excluded in an evaluation, analysis, or measurement of environmental impacts, sustainability performance, or related objectives

entities.name: Asset
entities.description: something of monetary value that is owned or provides benefit to some party

entities.name: AssetClass
entities.description: financial instrument classifier for a group of securities that exhibit similar characteristics, behave similarly in the marketplace and are subject to the same laws and regulations

entities.name: AssignableContract
entities.description: contract in which contract holder (assignor) may transfer some or all of their rights and obligations to another party (assignee)

entities.name: Association
entities.description: not-for-profit organization that is owned by and acts on behalf of its members

entities.name: AuctionDateRule
entities.description: business recurrence interval convention that is a published rule for defining the date of some auction event

entities.name: AuctionMarket
entities.description: exchange in which buyers and sellers submit competitive bids that do not involve direct negotiations between parties, as part of an auction scheduled either on demand or on a periodic basis

entities.name: Auditor
entities.description: party qualified and authorized to review and verify the accuracy of financial records and ensure that companies comply with tax laws

entities.name: AutomatedSystem
entities.description: system that reduces or eliminates the need for human involvement in order to complete a task

entities.name: AverageDailyEarnings
entities.description: measure of the average daily wage an employee makes over the reporting period

entities.name: AverageHourlyEarnings
entities.description: measure of the average hourly wage an employee makes over the reporting period

entities.name: AverageMonthlyEarnings
entities.description: measure of the average monthly wage an employee makes over the reporting period

entities.name: AverageWeeklyEarnings
entities.description: measure of the average weekly wage an employee makes over the reporting period

description._: method used for calculating the average rate or price of an Asian option

entities.name: Balance
entities.description: amount of money available or owed

entities.name: Bank
entities.description: depository institution, usually a corporation, that accepts deposits, makes loans, pays checks, and performs related services, for individual members of the public, businesses or other organizations

entities.name: BankHoldingCompany
entities.description: any company that owns and/or has direct or indirect control of one or more banks; BHCs may also own nonbanking subsidiaries such as broker-dealers and asset managers

entities.name: BankIdentifier
entities.description: identifier that uniquely identifies the financial institution and, when appropriate, the branch of that financial institution servicing an account

entities.name: BankingProduct
entities.description: product provided to consumers and businesses by a depository institution

description._: common metal that tarnishes, oxidizes, or corrodes relatively quickly when exposed to air or moisture, that is widely used in commercial and industrial applications, such as construction and manufacturing

entities.name: BaseRate
entities.description: basic rate of interest on which the actual rate a bank charges on loans to its customers is calculated

entities.name: BaseUnit
entities.description: measurement unit that is defined by a system of units to be the reference measurement unit for a base quantity

entities.name: Basket
entities.description: collection of goods, services, or other things (e.g., financial contracts) that can be purchased and sold in some marketplace

description._: credit default swap that references a bespoke, synthetic portfolio of underlying assets whose components have been agreed to for a specific OTC derivative by the parties to the transaction
futures contract whose underlying asset is a basket of securities and/or indices

entities.name: BeneficialOwner
entities.description: party that enjoys the benefits of ownership (such as receipt of income) of something even though its ownership (title) may be in the name of another party (called a nominee or registered owner)

entities.name: BeneficialOwnership
entities.description: control situation linking something at least one beneficial owner

entities.name: Beneficiary
entities.description: party that receives some benefit or advantage or profits from something

entities.name: BenefitCorporation
entities.description: not-for-profit corporation set up under specific state legislation, typically to provide some social benefit, without an obligation to maximize shareholder return

entities.name: BestEffortsOffering
entities.description: securities offering whereby investment bankers commit to doing their best to sell the securities offered, but do not assume the full risk of an underwriter

description._: an alpha-3 code that is a member of the set of bibliographic codes in ISO 639-2

entities.name: BilateralAgreement
entities.description: agreement where two parties commit to perform specific actions or obligations towards each other

entities.name: BilateralContract
entities.description: contract where two parties commit to perform specific actions or obligations towards each other

description._: short-term negotiable financial instrument consisting of an order in writing addressed by one person (the seller of goods) to another (the buyer), requiring the latter to pay a fixed amount of money on demand (a sight draft) or on a predetermined date (a time draft)

entities.name: BoardAgreement
entities.description: formal, legally binding agreement between members of the Board of Directors of the organization

entities.name: BoardCapacity
entities.description: authority to act in a fiduciary capacity with respect to the organization, including but not limited to determining and executing corporate policy

entities.name: BoardCompositionControl
entities.description: situation in which a voting shareholder, entity owner, or some other party in the case of a not-for-profit organization, appoints and/or nominates someone to the board of directors of an organization for some period of time

entities.name: BoardMember
entities.description: party that has fiduciary responsibility with respect to the organization, including but not limited to determining and executing corporate policy

entities.name: BoardMembership
entities.description: situation relating an individual member of the board of directors to the organization

entities.name: BoardOfDirectors
entities.description: group of people comprising the governing body of an organization that has the authority to set organizational strategy and policies as well as to select and, to some degree manage, leadership

entities.name: Bond
entities.description: tradable debt instrument representing a loan in which the issuer owes the holder(s) a debt

description._: futures contract whose underlying asset is at least one bond

entities.name: BondInsurance
entities.description: insurance policy that a bond issuer purchases that guarantees the repayment of the principal and all associated interest payments to the bondholders in the event of default

description._: purchase right that gives a prospective acquiree's bondholders the right to buy bonds of the firm or bonds of anyone who acquires the firm at a deep discount to their fair market value

entities.name: BondRegistrar
entities.description: party responsible for maintaining records on behalf of the issuer that identify the owners of a registered bond issue

entities.name: BondWithPublishedSinkingFund
entities.description: bond whereby amortization is via a known and published schedule

description._: financial institution (typically a commercial or investment bank) responsible for coordinating the arrangement, structuring, and marketing of the loan to potential lenders

entities.name: Borrower
entities.description: party to a credit agreement that is obligated to repay the amount borrowed (principal) with interest and other fees according to the terms of the instrument

entities.name: Branch
entities.description: part of a larger organization that might not be co-located with it

entities.name: BranchOfGovernment
entities.description: division of the government of a state, with separate and independent powers and areas of responsibility so that the powers of one branch are not in conflict with the powers associated with the other branches

description._: classifier of events representing breaking a promise specified in a contract to do or not to do something, without a legitimate excuse

entities.name: BrokerageAccount
entities.description: account offered by a broker that allows the investor to deposit funds and place investment orders

entities.name: BrokerageFirm
entities.description: firm in the business of buying and selling securities, operating as both a broker and a dealer, depending on the transaction

entities.name: BrokerDealer
entities.description: any party in the business of buying and selling securities, operating as both a broker and a dealer, depending on the transaction

entities.name: BuildAmericaBond
entities.description: taxable municipal bond issued through December 31, 2010 under the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act of 2009 (ARRA)

description._: physical precious metal that is officially recognized as being at least 99.5 percent pure

entities.name: BusinessCalendar
entities.description: schedule and communications tool used to manage meetings, plan events, and coordinate activities within and/or across organizations

entities.name: BusinessCenter
entities.description: municipality where business is conducted, especially one that is considered a financial center

entities.name: BusinessCenterCode
entities.description: code used to denote a metropolitan area where business is conducted

entities.name: BusinessCenterCodeScheme
entities.description: coding scheme used to define a set of codes for municipalities or business centers

entities.name: BusinessDayAdjustment
entities.description: BusinessDayAdjustment as defined in OWL ontology

entities.name: BusinessDayAdjustmentCode
entities.description: code used to denote a convention for specifying what happens when a date falls on a day that is weekend or holiday in some municipality or business center

entities.name: BusinessDayConvention
entities.description: convention that enumerates the possible ways to handle a date that falls on a weekend or holiday

entities.name: BusinessEntity
entities.description: entity that is formed and administered as per commercial law in order to engage in business activities

entities.name: BusinessIdentifierCode
entities.description: international identifier for financial and non-financial institutions used to facilitate automated processing of information for financial services

entities.name: BusinessIdentifierCodeScheme
entities.description: scheme that specifies the elements of a unique business identifier code (BIC) scheme to identify financial and non-financial institutions used to facilitate automated processing of information for financial services

entities.name: BusinessLicense
entities.description: license that allows the holder to conduct business or carry out a specific profession within some jurisdiction for some period of time

entities.name: BusinessObjective
entities.description: objective that reflects the strategic goals and direction of a business within a time frame and available resources

entities.name: BusinessPartyPrefix
entities.description: four-character (4 alphanumeric) code associated with an organization for the purposes of banking telecommunications

entities.name: BusinessPartySuffix
entities.description: two-character (2 alphanumeric) code associated with the organization for the purposes of banking telecommunications

entities.name: BusinessRecurrenceInterval
entities.description: recurrence interval that is defined per a specific convention that determines how recurring days should be handled

entities.name: BusinessRecurrenceIntervalConvention
entities.description: convention that specifies how recurring days should be handled, such as the end of the month, a particular day of the month, a day of the week, or more specifically, a t-bill auction date

entities.name: BusinessRegisterIdentifier
entities.description: identifier that uniquely identifies a business register, such as a register identified by the Global Legal Entity Identifier Foundation (GLEIF) registration authorities list

entities.name: BusinessRegistrationAuthority
entities.description: registration authority that is responsible for maintaining a registry of business entities

entities.name: BusinessRegistry
entities.description: registry for registering and maintaining information about business entities

entities.name: BusinessRegistryEntry
entities.description: entry in a business registry

entities.name: BusinessStrategy
entities.description: strategy for achieving a specific business goal, objective, solution or outcome

description._: classifier of corporate actions that involve improving liquidity or changing the overall structure of the organization through diversification, combining and closing parts of the business, etc, to increase long-term profitability
strategy that combines bull and bear spreads with a fixed risk and capped profit

entities.name: Buyer
entities.description: party that purchases something in exchange for money or other consideration under a contract of sale

entities.name: Bylaws
entities.description: written rules for conduct of a corporation, association, partnership or any organization

entities.name: Calculation
entities.description: actual execution of some computation, computational process, or operation that was scheduled or triggered by something

entities.name: CalculationEvent
entities.description: kind of event that is either scheduled or triggered by something, such as a related financial event, that causes a calculation to be performed

entities.name: CalculationPeriod
entities.description: explicit period from the start to the end of a specific interval or range within which a computational process or operation occurs

entities.name: CallableBond
entities.description: bond that includes a stipulation allowing the issuer the right to repurchase and retire the bond at the call price after the call protection period

description._: warrant giving the buyer (holder) the right, but not the obligation, to acquire specific underlying assets during a specified period at a specified price

entities.name: CanadianCreditUnion
entities.description: a not-for-profit financial institution, typically formed by the employees of a company, labor union, or religious group, operated as a cooperative association organized for the purpose of promoting thrift among its members and creating a source of credit for provident or productive purposes

entities.name: Capability
entities.description: ability to perform a specific function or achieve a particular outcome

description._: basket of debt instruments whose constituents are contracts entitling a renter the temporary use of an asset and, in accounting terms, has asset ownership characteristics

entities.name: CapitalLease
entities.description: lease that must be reflected on an organization's balance sheet as an asset and as a corresponding liability

description._: structured product that participates in the performance of a financial asset, such as a stock, fund or index, while protecting the investor's capital

entities.name: CapitalSurplus
entities.description: capital contributed in excess of the par value (stated value) of the ownership interest issued

entities.name: CardAccount
entities.description: account whose terms and conditions are defined in a card agreement that is represented by a payment card

entities.name: Cardholder
entities.description: account holder to whom a payment card is issued

entities.name: CardProduct
entities.description: financial product involving the issuance of credit, debit, or other payment cards

description._: strategy for calculating or otherwise establishing a reference final price for the contract

entities.name: Catalog
entities.description: publication including a list of products available for sale with their descriptions and possibly prices

entities.name: CentralSecuritiesDepository
entities.description: functional entity that provides a central point for depositing financial instruments ('securities'), for example, bonds and shares

entities.name: CharteredLegalPerson
entities.description: a legal person created by a royal charter or decree

entities.name: ChiefExecutiveOfficer
entities.description: top corporate officer responsible for an organization's overall operations and performance

entities.name: ChiefFinancialOfficer
entities.description: senior-most corporate officer responsible for financial control and planning for an organization or project

description._: exotic option that allows its holder (buyer) to exercise the right to buy (call) or sell (put) specified assets at a fixed price whereby the buyer does not have to decide whether the contract will be a put or a call until an agreed future date, prior to expiration

entities.name: Civilian
entities.description: person that is not a member of the military (i.e., that is not on active duty)

entities.name: CivilianNonInstitutionalPerson
entities.description: legal working-age person that does not live in an institution (for example, a correctional facility, long-term care hospital, or nursing home), and is not on active military duty

entities.name: CivilianNonInstitutionalPopulation
entities.description: statistical universe consisting of people of a certain age who reside in a given region, do not live in institutions (for example, correctional facilities, long-term care hospitals, and nursing homes), and are not on active military duty

entities.name: Claim
entities.description: demand or assertion made by one party on another, based on facts that, taken together, give rise to a legally enforceable right or judicial action

description._: corporate action involving a situation where interested parties seek restitution for financial loss

entities.name: ClassificationOfFinancialInstrumentsCodeScheme
entities.description: classification scheme for set of codes for financial instruments that can be used globally for straight-through processing by all involved participants in an electronic data processing environment

entities.name: Classifier
entities.description: standardized classification or delineation for something, per some scheme for such delineation, within a specified context

entities.name: ClearingBank
entities.description: commercial bank that facilitates payment and settlement of financial transactions, such as check clearing or facilitating trades between the sellers and buyers of securities or other financial instruments or contracts

entities.name: ClearingCorporation
entities.description: clearing house that is organized as a corporation

entities.name: ClearingService
entities.description: service provided on behalf of an institutional market participant by a clearing services provider following a trade that finalizes the transfer of security ownership

entities.name: Client
entities.description: party that purchases professional services from, or has a formal relationship to purchase services from another party

entities.name: ClientIdentifier
entities.description: sequence of characters uniquely identifying a client within the context of some organization

entities.name: ClosedEndCredit
entities.description: credit agreement in which the loan principal cannot be increased after funds are dispersed in full when the loan closes

description._: investment fund that has a fixed number of shares offered by an investment company through an initial public offering

entities.name: ClosedEndMortgageLoan
entities.description: loan secured by real estate with no ability for the borrower to receive additional funds under the loan at a later date

entities.name: ClosedEndReverseMortgage
entities.description: reverse mortgage that provides a lump sum payment to the borrower at closing, with no ability for the borrower to receive additional funds under the mortgage at a later date

entities.name: CoherentDerivedUnit
entities.description: derived unit that, for a given system of quantities and for a chosen set of base units, is a product of powers of base units with no other proportionality factor than one

description._: option trading strategy that involves buying a downside put and selling an upside call that is implemented to protect against large losses, but which also limits large upside gains

entities.name: Collateral
entities.description: something pledged as security to ensure fulfillment of an obligation to another party, to lend money, extend credit, or provision securities

entities.name: CollateralAgreement
entities.description: written contract related to another contract designed to provide clarity and additional protection for all parties involved, that is separate from the primary contract and that can be independently enforced

entities.name: CollateralizedGuaranty
entities.description: guaranty that takes the form of some asset that is pledged by a borrower to a lender (usually in return for a loan)

description._: secured loan that is secured with cash or other acceptable collateral (real property, securities or other assets) provided by the borrower as specified in the collateral agreement

entities.name: Collection
entities.description: grouping of things (may be zero) that have some shared significance

description._: assets pooled by investors whose share capital remains separate from the assets of the vehicle

purchase right that gives a prospective acquiree's holders of multiple securities the right to buy securities of the firm or securities of anyone who acquires the firm at a deep discount to their fair market value

entities.name: CommercialBank
entities.description: depository institution that engages in various financial services, such as accepting deposits and making loans

entities.name: CommercialCreditCardAgreement
entities.description: credit card agreement for a card issued to, or in conjunction with, a formal organization, such as a small business, middle market business, local, state, or national government, or large corporation

entities.name: CommercialFinanceCompany
entities.description: finance company that makes loans to manufacturers and wholesalers, secured by accounts receivable, inventories, and equipment

entities.name: CommercialLendingService
entities.description: service involving the extension of credit to support business activities

description._: loan extended to a corporation, commercial enterprise, joint venture, or other organization as opposed to a consumer

an unsecured short-term debt instrument typically issued by a bank, corporation, or foreign government to obtain funds to meet short-term debt obligations, such as accounts receivable, inventories, or payroll, backed only by an issuing bank or company promise to pay the face amount on the maturity date specified on the note

entities.name: Commitment
entities.description: promise made by some party to act or refrain from acting in some manner

entities.name: CommitmentAtLarge
entities.description: commitment made by some party without direct involvement from the potential beneficiaries of that commitment

description._: credit facility that is a confirmed source of financing for the borrower, as long as the borrower meets the conditions of the agreement
contractually committed portion of a credit facility that is available to the borrower and may be associated with some specific collateral

entities.name: Commodity
entities.description: material resource used in commerce that is interchangeable with other commodities of the same type

description._: forward contract in which a buyer and seller agree upon delivery of a specified quality and quantity of goods at a specified future date
investment vehicle that tracks a basket of commodities to measure their price and investment return performance

entities.name: CommodityInstrument
entities.description: financial instrument representing an ownership interest in bulk goods, such as raw materials and primary agricultural products

description._: contract that involves physical delivery of the commodity asset at settlement

entities.name: CommodityTradingAdvisor
entities.description: party that directly or indirectly advises others as to the value or advisability of buying or selling futures contracts or options

description._: purchase right that gives a prospective acquiree's common, convertible shareholders the right to buy common, convertible shares of the firm or common, convertible shares of anyone who acquires the firm at a deep discount to their fair market value

entities.name: CommonInterestDevelopmentCorporation
entities.description: not-for-profit corporation set up under specific state legislation as a business entity for homeowners' associations

entities.name: CommonShare
entities.description: share that signifies a unit of ownership in a corporation and represents a claim on part of the corporation's assets and earnings

description._: purchase right that gives a prospective acquiree's common shareholders the right to buy common shares of the firm or common shares of anyone who acquires the firm at a deep discount to their fair market value

entities.name: CompanyLaw
entities.description: legislation under which the formation, registration or incorporation, governance, and dissolution of a firm is administered and controlled

entities.name: CompanySecretary
entities.description: corporate officer appointed by the directors of an organization, responsible for ensuring compliance with legal obligations related to corporate governance

description._: equity warrant to purchase shares of capital stock issued by the corporation whose equity is the underlying asset

entities.name: Composition
entities.description: distinct thing resulting from bringing together other things, possibly in specific roles, for a particular purpose

description._: non-directional options strategy that limits both gains and losses while seeking to profit from either low or high volatility
corporate action that is a procedure that aims to obtain consent of holder to a proposal by the issuer or a third party without convening a meeting

entities.name: ConsolidatedTapeProvider
entities.description: data reporting services provider that is authorized to provide the service of collecting trade reports for financial instruments from regulated markets, MTFs, OTFs and APAs and consolidating them into a continuous electronic live data stream providing price and volume data per financial instrument

entities.name: Constant
entities.description: symbol that represents a value that does not change (i.e., is fixed) with respect to a formula or expression

entities.name: Constituent
entities.description: component of a collection or combination of things

entities.name: Constitution
entities.description: set of basic principles by which an organization is governed, especially in relation to the rights of the people it governs

entities.name: ConstitutionalOwner
entities.description: entity owner that holds an equity stake in said entity, in the form of shareholders' equity

entities.name: Consumer
entities.description: party that utilizes economic goods or services, typically for personal, family, or household purposes

entities.name: ConsumerCreditCardAgreement
entities.description: credit card agreement for a card issued for household, family, or other personal expenditures that is accessed by a borrower's use of a credit card

entities.name: ConsumerFinanceCompany
entities.description: finance company that lends to individuals under the small loans laws of the jurisdiction in which they operate

description._: loan to one or more individuals for household, family, or other personal expenditures, excluding mortgages and student loans

entities.name: Context
entities.description: situation or frame of reference in which something applies, exists, happens, or is used and that helps to illustrate or explain it

entities.name: ContingentObligation
entities.description: obligation that depends on a future event or the performance of an action

entities.name: ContingentRight
entities.description: right that depends on a future event or the performance of an action

entities.name: Contract
entities.description: voluntary, deliberate agreement between competent parties to which the parties agree to be legally bound, and for which the parties provide valuable consideration

description._: cash-settled derivative where the parties agree to exchange on the maturity of the contract the difference between the current value of the underlying asset and the initial value of that asset when the contract is initiated

entities.name: ContractLifecycle
entities.description: lifecycle of an agreement, including, but not limited to a credit agreement, financial instrument, or other formal contract, from initial stages through retirement

entities.name: ContractLifecycleEvent
entities.description: kind of event that occurs during one or more stages of the lifecycle of an agreement

entities.name: ContractLifecycleOccurrence
entities.description: realization of the lifecycle of a specific contract

entities.name: ContractLifecycleStage
entities.description: phase in the lifecycle of an agreement

entities.name: ContractLifecycleStageOccurrence
entities.description: realization, from start to finish of a phase in an occurrence of a specific contract lifecycle

entities.name: ContractParty
entities.description: legally competent party that has entered into a binding agreement, accepting and conceding obligations, responsibilities, and benefits as specified

entities.name: ContractPrincipal
entities.description: party that originates a contract and is identified as the first party to that contract, in the event that the contract distinguishes any party as such

entities.name: ContractThirdParty
entities.description: party that is indirectly involved in, but not a counterparty to, an agreement

entities.name: ContractualCapability
entities.description: the capacity to enter into legally binding contracts

entities.name: ContractualCommitment
entities.description: provision specifying something that the contracting parties agree to, i.e., a promise or pledge made by one of the parties to perform some action or fulfill some duty

entities.name: ContractualElement
entities.description: element, such as an arrangement, provision, requirement, rule, specification, and standard that forms an integral part of an agreement

entities.name: ContractuallyCapableEntity
entities.description: a unique entity that is legally or financially responsible for the performance of financial transactions, or has the legal right in its jurisdiction to enter independently into legal contracts, regardless of whether it is incorporated or constituted in some other way (e.g. trust, partnership, contractual). This excludes natural persons, but includes governmental organizations and supranationals.

entities.name: ContractualOption
entities.description: contractual right that may be exercised at some point in the future, such as an option to extend a contract, or other available but not obligatory rights as defined in the contract

entities.name: ContractualProduct
entities.description: product that takes the form of an agreement

entities.name: ContractualRight
entities.description: power, privilege, demand, or claim possessed by some party that is conferred by contract

entities.name: ContractualSavingsInstitution
entities.description: financial institution that provides the opportunity for individuals to invest in collective investment vehicles in a fiduciary rather than a principle role

entities.name: ContractualTemplateProduct
entities.description: contractual product that is finalized through specification of values for parameters defined in a template
